    Translator: Amitendranath Tagore
By: Ou-yang Hsiu
Title: The Middle Peak
---
You look but cannot reach,
You walk, the road goes twisting.
A path appears on the wood top;
A thousand cliffs are visible beneath the clouds.
Fog and mist gleamed, now it is dark again.
The last glow lingers on the peak's tip.
